## dev ‚Äî Full Development Cycle
{{if not .IsFullMode}}
> dev is Full mode only. Upgrade with `auto init --full`.
{{else}}
Execute the complete plan ‚Üí go ‚Üí sync cycle in one command.

### Pipeline

#### [REQUIRED] Stage 1: Plan (MUST call plan subcommand)

Run the `plan` pipeline with the feature description. Extract the SPEC-ID from the output.

Display after completion:
```
üêô Workflow: {SPEC-ID}
  ‚óè plan  ‚Üí  ‚óã go  ‚Üí  ‚óã sync
```

> **‚è≠ POST-STAGE**: plan complete, SPEC-ID extracted. NEXT REQUIRED STAGE: Stage 2: Go. Do NOT skip to Completion.

#### [REQUIRED] Stage 2: Go (MUST call go subcommand)

Run the `go` pipeline with `--auto --loop` flags using the SPEC-ID from Stage 1.

Display after completion:
```
üêô Workflow: {SPEC-ID}
  ‚úì plan  ‚Üí  ‚óè go  ‚Üí  ‚óã sync
```

> **‚è≠ POST-STAGE**: go complete. NEXT REQUIRED STAGE: Stage 3: Sync. Do NOT skip to Completion.

#### [REQUIRED] Stage 3: Sync (MUST call sync subcommand)

Run the `sync` pipeline with the SPEC-ID.

Display after completion:
```
üêô Workflow: {SPEC-ID}
  ‚úì plan  ‚Üí  ‚úì go  ‚Üí  ‚óè sync
```

### [REQUIRED] Pre-Completion Verification

Before displaying the final milestone output, verify ALL stages were completed:

- [ ] Stage 1: plan ‚Äî SPEC-ID created
- [ ] Stage 2: go ‚Äî implementation pipeline completed
- [ ] Stage 3: sync ‚Äî documentation synchronized, Lore commit made

IF any item is unchecked ‚Üí return to that stage. Do NOT display the milestone box.

### Flags

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--team` | Run `go` with Agent Teams (experimental) |
| `--solo` | Run `go` in single session mode (no subagents) |
| `--quality` | Quality mode: ultra or balanced |
| `--multi` | Enable multi-provider review in all stages |

Usage: `/auto dev "feature description"`, `/auto dev "feature description" --team`, `/auto dev "feature description" --quality ultra`
